## HARD RULES - VIOLATION = STOP AND REPORT

### R1 - No file creation without checking PROJECT_MAP.md
File already exists but recreate = conflict, broken import paths, duplicate logic.
â†’ Always grep PROJECT_MAP.md before `touch` any new file.

### R2 - No import path changes without updating all consumers
Check "Consumers" column in PROJECT_MAP.md. Changing 1 file = check all downstream consumers.

### R3 - No cryptographic primitive changes without test vectors
Applies to: hash functions, signature format, field encoding, byte order.
â†’ Must have concrete input/output test PASS before merge.

### R4 - NO `allocUnsafe`, `|`, `&` (bitwise) in any context
- TypeScript: `Buffer.alloc` NOT `allocUnsafe`, `&&` NOT `&`, `||` NOT `|`
- Cairo: `&&` NOT `&`, `||` NOT `|`
â†’ Rule 4 from PRD. Grep all files after writing.

### R5 - NO hardcoded cryptographic values by retyping
Use constants defined in `src/shared/utils.ts`. NEVER recalculate `BN254_PRIME`.

### R6 - `pubkey_x` and `pubkey_y` (BTC) are ABSOLUTELY PRIVATE
NEVER pass to Cairo contract. NEVER log. NEVER expose via public interface.
Bitcoin address leaks on-chain if violated.

### R7 - `buildProverInputs()` must be `async`, all callers must `await`
`computeNullifierHash()` is async (Poseidon lazy init). Missing `await` = Promise object instead of bigint = silent proof failure.

### R8 - `timestamp` ONLY from `relayerResponse.timestamp`
NEVER use `Date.now()`. NEVER use `new Date()`. Only `relayerResponse.timestamp`.
Wrong source = Cairo freshness check fail (3600s window).

### R9 - Poseidon input order is IMMUTABLE: `[secret, x_hi, x_lo, badge_type]`
TypeScript and Noir must match 1-to-1. Changing order = nullifier mismatch = proof fail.
Check INVARIANTS.md Poseidon section before touching anything related.

### R10 - `circomlibjs` must be pinned EXACT version `0.1.7`
NO `^0.1.7` or `~0.1.7`. Different version = different Poseidon output = proof fail.

